tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All measured laboratory values are within normal limits for this 79-year-old female patient. No evidence of renal, electrolyte, or glycemic abnormalities is present. The results indicate stable metabolic and renal function, and there are no acute concerns from a laboratory perspective at this time.
